        <abstract>
            <p>Has been able to do nothing in science of late due to illness [of Henrietta].</p> 
<p>When JDD reads <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>, CD knows he will be opposed to it, but he will be liberal and philosophical, which is more than he can say for his English opponents.</p> 
            <p>Has not yet seen L. Agassiz’s attack, but in principle avoids answering.</p> 
<p>No one understands <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> so well as Asa Gray.</p> 
            <p>At BAAS meeting at Oxford, CD’s side seems almost to have got the best of the battle.</p>
        </abstract>
